{
  "text": "Adipose cells found in greater quantity in tumor tissues of obese-MSG rats also may have contributed to the increased tumor development in this group. Adipose cells produce and release several factors, such as leptin, IL-6 and TNF-alpha, which stimulate cell proliferation and tumor angiogenesis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , thus contributing to a better microenvironment for tumor development.",
  "correct_citation": {
